CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 29, 1958, pg. 8, reads: "Attention State Liquor Control Board - How Many More Taverns Can Homewood-Brushton Stand?  'The Other One' - The second of two taverns within two consecutive blocks on the fringe of Homewood-Brushton bordering boundary lines of Wilkinsburg and Penn Township is the Oakwood Tavern in the 7900 block of Frankstown Ave.... - All Photos by Harris."
TitMainTitle: 7900 block of Frankstown Avenue with Reliable Drug store, Oakwood Tavern, and Vince's Supermarket, Homewood
